author: Written by: Sam Winstrom, Assignment Editor
title: 'Suspicious item' discovered on New Orleans plane bound for Phoe
text:
NEW ORLEANS (WVUE) - Local authorities were called to MSY airport after pilots discovered a "suspicious item" on a Phoenix-bound plane.
According to Southwest Airlines, the pilots of flight #2029 called local authorities after finding a "suspicious item" on the plane just before 7 p.m. on Oct. 15. The plane has since been cleared of any threat.
There were 134 customers set to board the plane to Phoenix according to Southwest. They will now board a different aircraft to Phoenix and are expected to arrive about four hours after their originally scheduled time.
